VIENTIANE TIMES, 3 June 2016, The National Assembly yesterday adopted the law on the state lottery, making it legal.

A shop owner selling lottery tickets. The approving of the new law allows state-owned Lottery Companies to establish lottery companies for selling lottery tickets to people 18 years old or older.

The law was approved during the NA’s first sitting on May 2, but yesterday’s sitting saw the legal formalities.

The signing of contracts and implementation of the law will depend on whether the NA’s capable committee and the government can work together to discuss and put in place specific strategies to implement it in line with the law.

National Assembly Vice President and chair of the justice and law committee Sinthasone Xayalath said several points were raised during yesterday's session for consideration during the law's implementation.

The advisability Sitthavong Radouangdeth wants the government to submit a budget request with a plan from the Ministry of Public Security, the Ministry of Home Affairs and the Ministry of Finance for each job.

He also wants the state lotteries to have clear targets for the people that they help and a supervisory system.

The NA member wrote in his letter that the lotteries needed to find criteria, a timeframe and a budget for each operation and each supported group.

The member also noted that each listed reference would have to select a candidate committee for verification, allocate funding for scholarship recipients and agree on a timeframe.
